<p>Hello there, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fish-salad-man" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6648529); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6648529&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1604609834" alt="Fish Salad Man" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6648529)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fish-salad-man" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6648529); return false;">Fish Salad Man</a></span>. Welcome to the SCP Wiki!</p>
<p>Glad to see you're interested in writing for the wiki. Honestly, coldposting isn't a good idea. First of all, you should read around a bit to gauge what people are into and what's wanted. I personally suggest checking out <a href="/scp-5005">SCP-5005</a>. Either way, if you just coldpost, you'll be likely to not succeed. Anyway, check out these resources so you can improve your writing and to avoid just coldposting:</p>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">◎&nbsp;Open&nbsp;Resources&nbsp;◎</a></div>
