<p>Good day, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tribal-machination" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6972505); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6972505&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606076379" alt="Tribal Machination" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6972505)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tribal-machination" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6972505); return false;">Tribal Machination</a></span>. Welcome to the SCP Wiki!</p>
<p>Glad to see you're interested in writing for the site. Industrial machinery is really cool, and if you ever want to find people who have similar interests, I recommend you check out our <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/chat-guide">IRC chatrooms</a> where you can talk with everyone. Reading around before jumping into writing immediately's a good idea. Particularly, since you plan on becoming an author, you should read a lot of the newer articles to get a feel for what the on-site community is interested in these days. I personally suggest checking out <a href="/scp-5762">SCP-5762</a>. Anyway, here's some resources that'll help you out around the site:</p>
