			<div class="content" id="post-content-4825713">
									

<p>Hey Spicy Sandwitch, welcome aboard! We are all here to have fun, so don't stress too much about writing these things. The staff and other members here are always very helpful when you need to refine an idea or get some help with details. References are always cool, as long as they're tasteful! Hope to see some of your work soon!<br />
As for writing, just make sure you go through the proper greenlighting process on the idea forums first. Remember that there is no rush, and you should take time familiarizing yourself with how Series 6 articles are formatted. We are a rather unique bunch so I'm sure just reading and being a part of the community will be rather fun for you! For my recommendation, you should check out <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-5095">SCP-4991</a> its an interesting SCP, that leaves me wanting to know more about what happened.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
